Antenna without scales. Antennal length to head diagonal length ratio (head diagonal measured from cervical edge to apex of mouth part) ≈ 1.3. Relation of antennal joints I–IV as 1:2:2:3. Dorsal Ant.I-organ present. Ant.III organ composed of two sub-cylindrical sensory rods partially covered by integumentary fold.Ant.IV with subapical mushroom-shaped chaeta (
T-chaeta
), without apical bulb.

Ventral tube without scales, with 12+12 ciliated chaetae on anterior side (
Fig. 33
) and 10 ciliated chaetae on posterior side; each lateral flap with maximum of 8 ciliated chaetae and 5 smooth chaetae.
